WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.200 --> 00:00:08.760
A NETFLIX SERIES

2
00:00:10.160 --> 00:00:12.160
<i>Aww. </i>[woman coos]

3
00:00:12.240 --> 00:00:13.360
[clicks tongue]

4
00:00:13.880 --> 00:00:15.480
[coos. laughs]

5
00:00:16.280 --> 00:00:17.320
[coos]

6
00:00:25.320 --> 00:00:27.840
[man] <i>I'm gonna get you!
I'm right behind you!</i>

7
00:00:28.600 --> 00:00:30.440
[man laughs] <i>I'm gonna get you now!</i>

8
00:00:32.360 --> 00:00:33.360
<i>Hold this.</i>

9
00:00:36.280 --> 00:00:37.680
<i>Over here. Adam!</i>

10
00:00:41.640 --> 00:00:42.640
ADAM. 6 YEARS

11
00:00:42.720 --> 00:00:47.000
<i>♪ Happy birthday to you
Happy birthday to you ♪</i>

12
00:00:47.080 --> 00:00:50.160
<i>♪ Happy birthday. dear Adam ♪</i>

13
00:00:50.240 --> 00:00:52.200
<i>♪ Happy birthday to you ♪</i>

14
00:00:52.280 --> 00:00:53.400
[woman cheers]

15
00:00:53.480 --> 00:00:55.080
[happy. excited chatter]

16
00:00:59.800 --> 00:01:01.800
[applause]

17
00:01:07.440 --> 00:01:08.440
<i>Hi-yah!</i>

18
00:01:08.960 --> 00:01:10.600
<i>Hi-yah! Hi-yah!</i>

19
00:01:11.800 --> 00:01:13.880
[man] <i>Nice to meet you. samurai Adam.</i>

20
00:01:18.760 --> 00:01:19.760
[boy grunts]

21
00:01:20.360 --> 00:01:22.680
<i>Who's stronger than me. huh? Ha!</i>

22
00:01:22.760 --> 00:01:23.880
<i>You lost. Igor.</i>

23
00:01:23.960 --> 00:01:24.960
[Igor] <i>Rematch?</i>

24
00:01:27.360 --> 00:01:29.920
[woman] <i>Sometimes it feels like
you're running off a cliff.</i>

25
00:01:30.000 --> 00:01:31.720
<i>Like in those cartoons.</i>

26
00:01:32.560 --> 00:01:34.000
The coyote near the edge.

27
00:01:34.080 --> 00:01:37.840
<i>he looks down and instantly knows
he's made a mistake.</i>

28
00:01:37.920 --> 00:01:39.160
<i>But it's too late.</i>

29
00:01:42.000 --> 00:01:43.800
<i>Kids grow up fast.</i>

30
00:01:44.800 --> 00:01:47.400
<i>And you think
that they're far from the edge.</i>

31
00:01:47.920 --> 00:01:49.600
<i>They still worship their parents.</i>

32
00:01:51.920 --> 00:01:55.360
<i>But all of a sudden.
something unexpected happens...</i>

33
00:01:59.840 --> 00:02:03.400
<i>and you realize
we're no longer their gods.</i>

34
00:02:05.200 --> 00:02:08.080
<i>We can keep them away
from the edge for a while.</i>

35
00:02:10.040 --> 00:02:11.840
<i>but then they're on their own.</i>

36
00:02:14.480 --> 00:02:20.720
<i>All I want is to keep my son safe
till the time comes to let him go.</i>

37
00:02:21.680 --> 00:02:22.920
<i>And after that...</i>

38
00:02:23.520 --> 00:02:25.480
- [computer chimes]
<i>- ...it's up to him.</i>

39
00:02:25.560 --> 00:02:26.880
[footsteps approach]

40
00:02:26.960 --> 00:02:29.960
[man] Why are you still awake. hon?
You know what time it is?

41
00:02:30.040 --> 00:02:32.120
- Come on.
- I'm worried about Adam.

42
00:02:34.560 --> 00:02:35.560
[man sighs]

43
00:02:36.440 --> 00:02:37.760
So what are you up to?

44
00:02:39.680 --> 00:02:40.680
[man grunts]

45
00:02:43.440 --> 00:02:44.880
Is that his cell phone?

46
00:02:44.960 --> 00:02:47.520
- Are you installing spyware?
- Just to know he's all right.

47
00:02:47.600 --> 00:02:48.600
[man sighs]

48
00:02:49.800 --> 00:02:51.480
- [sighs]
- Have you talked to him?

49
00:02:52.600 --> 00:02:56.240
What's the point? He would just use
one of his friends' phones.

50
00:02:56.320 --> 00:02:59.240
So you're gonna read his text messages?
His emails?

51
00:02:59.320 --> 00:03:03.640
- His conversations with his girlfriend?
- Michał... Adam's not well.

52
00:03:06.200 --> 00:03:07.200
[sighs]

53
00:03:14.320 --> 00:03:15.320
[sighs]

54
00:03:16.680 --> 00:03:18.400
It's only been a few weeks
since Igor died.

55
00:03:18.480 --> 00:03:22.720
- I know.
- Most kids wouldn't be back to normal.

56
00:03:23.640 --> 00:03:25.400
But he's in trouble. I know it.

57
00:03:28.080 --> 00:03:30.480
- [sighs]
- Uninstall it. okay? Delete it.

58
00:03:30.560 --> 00:03:33.560
Let's wait. I need to know
if something's going on with him.

59
00:03:35.000 --> 00:03:37.040
It's our responsibility
to protect our child.

60
00:03:37.120 --> 00:03:38.240
I know something's up.

61
00:03:39.120 --> 00:03:41.080
He's our child. We should trust him.

62
00:03:41.160 --> 00:03:44.520
Anna. come on. Don't do this. It's crazy.

63
00:03:45.320 --> 00:03:47.440
We all have our own little secrets. right?

64
00:03:47.520 --> 00:03:51.200
- [scoffs] Well. I really don't.
- It's not like I keep secrets from you.

65
00:03:51.280 --> 00:03:53.440
I just don't need you to know
everything I'm thinking.

66
00:03:53.520 --> 00:03:55.400
That's not why I'm doing it. Michał.

67
00:03:55.920 --> 00:03:58.440
- I'm not being nosy.
- Okay. then uninstall it.

68
00:03:58.520 --> 00:04:01.880
- I'm doing it 'cause I love him.
- Uninstall it. I'm going to sleep.

69
00:04:04.760 --> 00:04:05.760
[Anna sighs]

70
00:04:11.280 --> 00:04:13.440
[mid-tempo rock music
playing in background]

71
00:04:15.000 --> 00:04:21.074
Do you want subtitles for any video?
-=[ ai.OpenSubtitles.com ]=-

72
00:04:26.360 --> 00:04:29.280
[man Too shallow. Too simplistic.

73
00:04:29.360 --> 00:04:30.480
[woman] I know. Stop.

74
00:04:30.560 --> 00:04:32.160
[man] Seriously. it's not fair.

75
00:04:32.240 --> 00:04:34.200
- All right.
- You're being ridiculous.

76
00:04:35.240 --> 00:04:37.280
- No. I'm enlightened.
- Uh-huh.

77
00:04:37.360 --> 00:04:38.480
Two beers. please.

78
00:04:42.000 --> 00:04:44.480
We can just switch seats.
if you two are having a conversation.

79
00:04:44.520 --> 00:04:46.840
- No. it's all good.
- Yeah. it's not a problem.

80
00:04:46.920 --> 00:04:50.040
Besides. you never really know.
You might learn something.

81
00:04:51.440 --> 00:04:53.200
Take. for instance. Adam and Eve.

82
00:04:53.720 --> 00:04:55.480
You buy that silly Bible story?

83
00:04:56.080 --> 00:05:00.600
Uh. sure. She was the first woman.
and he was the first man.

84
00:05:00.680 --> 00:05:04.000
- Uh-huh.
- Anyway... what about it?

85
00:05:05.480 --> 00:05:07.960
They had two sons
named Cain and Abel.

86
00:05:09.080 --> 00:05:11.320
Abel killed his brother Cain. right?

87
00:05:11.400 --> 00:05:12.400
[scoffs]

88
00:05:14.400 --> 00:05:16.160
But Cain's the one who killed Abel.

89
00:05:16.240 --> 00:05:17.440
- [man] Really?
- I thought so.

90
00:05:19.040 --> 00:05:21.440
[man] Either way.
there was one brother left.

91
00:05:22.040 --> 00:05:23.520
Which brings up the question.

92
00:05:23.600 --> 00:05:26.240
who'd the son procreate with
so humans would thrive?

93
00:05:27.120 --> 00:05:28.120
Just to give you a hint.

94
00:05:28.160 --> 00:05:30.440
the only other female around
was his own mother.

95
00:05:30.520 --> 00:05:33.040
[woman] Maybe they had
one more child. A girl.

96
00:05:33.120 --> 00:05:34.976
- Mm-hmm.
- Who they didn't mention in the Bible.

97
00:05:35.000 --> 00:05:36.400
Oh. then he fucked his own sister?

98
00:05:36.480 --> 00:05:39.080
- Stop it. Just stop it.
- What do you mean. stop it?

99
00:05:39.160 --> 00:05:41.560
People used to do. uh. strange things.

100
00:05:41.640 --> 00:05:44.240
People still do
pretty strange things. I'd say.

101
00:05:46.640 --> 00:05:48.040
Don't cry. sweetheart.

102
00:05:50.080 --> 00:05:51.360
Don't touch me.

103
00:05:52.520 --> 00:05:54.680
Your eyes are red. I was just concerned.

104
00:05:55.200 --> 00:05:56.720
You sure you're all right?

105
00:05:56.800 --> 00:05:58.440
I just want to drink alone.

106
00:05:59.320 --> 00:06:00.400
All right.

107
00:06:02.680 --> 00:06:03.960
You suit yourself.

108
00:06:05.080 --> 00:06:06.080
[pop song continues]

109
00:06:15.480 --> 00:06:17.480
[foreboding music playing]

110
00:06:25.800 --> 00:06:26.800
Hey!

111
00:06:28.040 --> 00:06:29.040
Are you okay?

112
00:06:29.960 --> 00:06:32.040
Hey. you're all right. Lean on me.

113
00:06:34.720 --> 00:06:35.720
Let's go.

114
00:06:36.320 --> 00:06:37.760
One step at a time.

115
00:06:41.800 --> 00:06:42.800
Hi. Marianna.

116
00:06:43.440 --> 00:06:44.600
Where's the tape?

117
00:06:47.400 --> 00:06:48.520
Let's go.

118
00:06:54.600 --> 00:06:57.160
[Marianna struggling]

119
00:07:08.320 --> 00:07:12.840
BASED ON THE NOVEL BY HARLAN COBEN

120
00:07:17.200 --> 00:07:19.600
- [tense music subsides]
- [coffee maker whirs]

121
00:07:19.680 --> 00:07:20.680
[beeps]

122
00:07:30.920 --> 00:07:31.920
[grunts]

123
00:07:34.920 --> 00:07:37.280
[DJ] <i>For your chance to win. stay tuned.</i>

124
00:07:37.360 --> 00:07:40.840
<i>And if you have information
to share about traffic. just call us.</i>

125
00:07:40.920 --> 00:07:42.760
[instructor calling out in Japanese]

126
00:07:49.240 --> 00:07:50.800
[all crying out]

127
00:07:55.680 --> 00:07:56.880
[man] Excellent!

128
00:07:57.800 --> 00:07:59.440
[intense music playing]

129
00:08:41.480 --> 00:08:42.936
- [woman] Good job.
- [man] Very good.

130
00:08:42.960 --> 00:08:43.960
[music continues]

131
00:08:44.880 --> 00:08:48.560
[man] Yeah. it'll start to come easier
after you try out these next steps.

132
00:08:48.640 --> 00:08:49.840
Trust me.

133
00:08:49.920 --> 00:08:51.760
[woman] Yeah. I hope so.

134
00:08:53.360 --> 00:08:55.040
[indistinct chattering]

135
00:08:55.120 --> 00:08:57.000
- [phone chimes]
- [woman] Yeah. got it.

136
00:08:59.200 --> 00:09:01.200
WIOSNA HOUSING ESTATE

137
00:09:09.080 --> 00:09:11.240
PRODUCE STORE

138
00:09:11.320 --> 00:09:12.640
[door chimes]

139
00:09:14.000 --> 00:09:15.000
Good morning.

140
00:09:15.360 --> 00:09:17.280
- Hey.
- Good morning. Anna.

141
00:09:18.600 --> 00:09:19.600
[grunts]

142
00:09:21.400 --> 00:09:25.040
Training every morning at 6:00 a.m.?
I don't think I could do that.

143
00:09:25.640 --> 00:09:27.880
You'll never know if you never try.

144
00:09:30.480 --> 00:09:31.480
Ola's gonna sleep over?

145
00:09:32.440 --> 00:09:33.680
She's really excited.

146
00:09:34.480 --> 00:09:35.480
[phone chimes]

147
00:09:36.640 --> 00:09:37.640
Just a sec.

148
00:09:42.720 --> 00:09:44.080
SPYWARE

149
00:09:44.160 --> 00:09:46.680
ADAM: HE WAS MY FRIEND

150
00:09:46.760 --> 00:09:49.680
BELIEVE ME. IT WAS MY FAULT

151
00:09:50.440 --> 00:09:52.800
KAJA: COME ON. STOP BLAMING YOURSELF

152
00:09:53.520 --> 00:09:56.520
ADAM: I DON'T KNOW IF I CAN

153
00:10:00.160 --> 00:10:03.280
KAJA: STAY POSITIVE. SEE YOU AT SCHOOL

154
00:10:14.200 --> 00:10:15.480
- See ya.
- Bye.

155
00:10:20.680 --> 00:10:23.360
[girl] Adam! Hurry up!

156
00:10:24.240 --> 00:10:26.440
Why can't you use the other bathroom?

157
00:10:26.520 --> 00:10:28.480
[girl] Because all my stuff's in there.

158
00:10:32.000 --> 00:10:33.800
- You little twerp.
- Jerk!

159
00:10:46.560 --> 00:10:47.560
Come look at this.

160
00:10:47.640 --> 00:10:51.280
Nice to see you too. hon.
You get your butt kicked at the gym?

161
00:10:51.360 --> 00:10:54.240
We said we wouldn't do this.
I thought you agreed with me.

162
00:10:58.000 --> 00:11:00.480
He's texting in the middle of the night
instead of sleeping.

163
00:11:00.920 --> 00:11:02.280
Kids do that all the time.

164
00:11:03.760 --> 00:11:05.080
He's texting about Igor.

165
00:11:05.160 --> 00:11:08.480
[man] Because he was his best friend.
I'm not at all surprised.

166
00:11:09.040 --> 00:11:11.800
He's already tried to run away once.
I'm not gonna let...

167
00:11:12.480 --> 00:11:14.080
- Hi. sweetheart.
- Hey.

168
00:11:16.920 --> 00:11:19.240
- Hey. eat something.
- I'm not hungry.

169
00:11:19.320 --> 00:11:21.360
[man] Want a ride to school?

170
00:11:21.440 --> 00:11:23.440
- [Adam] No. that's fine. I'm good.
- Adam.

171
00:11:24.200 --> 00:11:25.200
Adam!

172
00:11:27.040 --> 00:11:28.600
I'll see you later at the memorial?

173
00:11:28.680 --> 00:11:29.680
Mm-hmm.

174
00:11:32.840 --> 00:11:34.840
[mysterious music playing]

175
00:11:36.680 --> 00:11:38.480
- There's something wrong.
- [door closes]

176
00:11:38.560 --> 00:11:41.360
He disappears for days. He skips class.
He doesn't answer his phone.

177
00:11:41.440 --> 00:11:44.440
- He's been like this since Igor died.
- He's a teenager.

178
00:11:44.520 --> 00:11:46.960
Did your parents always know
what you were up to?

179
00:11:48.080 --> 00:11:49.080
Anna...

180
00:11:50.400 --> 00:11:52.080
all of us keep some secrets. huh?

181
00:12:03.560 --> 00:12:05.200
["Sleepwalker" by Coals plays]

182
00:12:18.040 --> 00:12:20.400
<i>♪ Mama. I have no time ♪</i>

183
00:12:20.480 --> 00:12:23.000
<i>♪ Looking for the root of problems ♪</i>

184
00:12:23.080 --> 00:12:25.280
<i>♪ Mama. I have no time ♪</i>

185
00:12:25.360 --> 00:12:27.760
<i>♪ Looking for the root of problems ♪</i>

186
00:12:29.360 --> 00:12:32.480
<i>♪ I know I should be afraid of night ♪</i>

187
00:12:34.360 --> 00:12:37.560
<i>♪ My... my little poly state of mind ♪</i>

188
00:12:38.080 --> 00:12:40.080
Here you go. Nika. Have a good day.

189
00:12:40.160 --> 00:12:42.880
<i>♪ I know I should be afraid of night ♪</i>

190
00:12:44.400 --> 00:12:47.440
<i>♪ My... my little poly state of mind ♪</i>

191
00:12:48.080 --> 00:12:50.480
<i>♪ Mama. I have no time ♪</i>

192
00:12:50.560 --> 00:12:52.960
<i>♪ Looking for the root of problems ♪</i>

193
00:12:53.040 --> 00:12:55.480
<i>♪ Mama. I have no time ♪</i>

194
00:12:55.560 --> 00:12:57.960
<i>♪ Looking for the root of problems ♪</i>

195
00:12:58.040 --> 00:12:59.800
[song fades away]

196
00:13:02.560 --> 00:13:05.520
Okay. Pop quiz.
Who was the first king of Poland?

197
00:13:06.320 --> 00:13:08.160
- Stanisław the Brave.
- Bolesław.

198
00:13:08.920 --> 00:13:11.160
The baptism of Poland. What year was that?

199
00:13:11.240 --> 00:13:12.480
- Ola.
- What?

200
00:13:13.520 --> 00:13:14.680
Focus. It was 966.

201
00:13:14.760 --> 00:13:17.480
You have a midterm.
A test you're not allowed to skip.

202
00:13:18.080 --> 00:13:20.320
How old was Jadwiga
when she took the throne?

203
00:13:21.360 --> 00:13:22.600
Jaśmina isn't answering.

204
00:13:23.160 --> 00:13:25.040
Maybe she forgot her phone. Focus!

205
00:13:25.720 --> 00:13:28.040
Jadwiga was 10.
She got married at your age.

206
00:13:28.120 --> 00:13:29.120
Not good for her!

207
00:13:29.840 --> 00:13:30.840
[phone chimes]

208
00:13:31.840 --> 00:13:33.520
NEW NOTIFICATION

209
00:13:39.600 --> 00:13:40.600
[car horn honks]

210
00:13:46.840 --> 00:13:48.040
Jaśmina!

211
00:13:50.560 --> 00:13:52.280
We're going to be late for school!

212
00:13:53.320 --> 00:13:55.320
- [sirens wailing in distance]
- [sighs]

213
00:14:10.240 --> 00:14:11.240
[man sighs]

214
00:14:16.200 --> 00:14:17.200
[man] You okay?

215
00:14:20.160 --> 00:14:21.840
They've been doing it again.

216
00:14:23.200 --> 00:14:24.960
That's enough of this stupid phone.

217
00:14:33.880 --> 00:14:35.800
[Jaśmina on phone] <i>Stop! What...</i>

218
00:14:35.880 --> 00:14:37.160
[mocking laughter on phone]

219
00:14:37.240 --> 00:14:39.360
[Jaśmina] <i>What do you want? Just stop it!</i>

220
00:14:51.280 --> 00:14:54.040
- [student] Good morning.
- Good morning. See you in the classroom.

221
00:15:00.200 --> 00:15:02.280
[Jaśmina] <i>What do you want? Just stop it!</i>

222
00:15:03.680 --> 00:15:06.440
- [laughter]
- [Jaśmina] <i>What do you want? Just stop it!</i>

223
00:15:07.400 --> 00:15:11.200
Kids have been circulating this video
since yesterday. "The bearded lady."

224
00:15:11.800 --> 00:15:14.320
[scoffs] You really called her that?

225
00:15:15.280 --> 00:15:16.480
Obviously. I did not.

226
00:15:18.120 --> 00:15:20.200
I was just telling a joke about beards.

227
00:15:20.280 --> 00:15:22.560
Kids must've twisted
what I was trying to say.

228
00:15:23.400 --> 00:15:24.400
And that's all?

229
00:15:26.000 --> 00:15:29.240
I've spoken to Jaśmina and apologized.
In front of the kids.

230
00:15:29.760 --> 00:15:32.200
What more can I do
to make this right. hmm?

231
00:15:46.880 --> 00:15:49.400
- Hello. there.
- Good morning.

232
00:15:52.720 --> 00:15:55.920
[student] Mm-hmm. Put it here. like this.

233
00:15:57.240 --> 00:15:59.240
[tense music playing]

234
00:16:04.840 --> 00:16:09.200
MEMORIAL AT 3:00 P.M. TODAY.
MONDAY. JUNE 7

235
00:16:09.280 --> 00:16:10.720
None of this is your fault.

236
00:16:11.200 --> 00:16:12.320
Oh. really?

237
00:16:12.400 --> 00:16:14.040
Adam. it was just an accident.

238
00:16:16.480 --> 00:16:19.320
Igor took pills
and washed them down with some wine.

239
00:16:19.400 --> 00:16:21.760
And the heart attack was
just bad luck. Adam.

240
00:16:22.560 --> 00:16:23.880
You weren't even with him.

241
00:16:31.840 --> 00:16:33.240
[Adam] He hated that photo.

242
00:16:37.240 --> 00:16:38.880
[school bell ringing]

243
00:16:38.960 --> 00:16:40.760
Boo!

244
00:16:40.840 --> 00:16:42.360
What's up? You coming?

245
00:16:54.960 --> 00:16:56.080
Gajewicz.

246
00:16:57.160 --> 00:16:58.280
Eyes on your paper.

247
00:17:05.160 --> 00:17:07.360
[foreboding music plays]

248
00:17:16.720 --> 00:17:17.760
It's a kneecap injury.

249
00:17:17.840 --> 00:17:19.160
- [phone chimes]
- Excuse me.

250
00:17:24.520 --> 00:17:26.400
[mouthing silently]

251
00:17:26.480 --> 00:17:27.480
[phone chimes]

252
00:17:39.680 --> 00:17:40.720
- What up?
- [grunts]

253
00:17:42.320 --> 00:17:43.560
- Hey!
- [Adam grunts]

254
00:17:43.640 --> 00:17:46.920
- Let go! I was just fucking around.
- You wanna try me. Gajos?

255
00:17:47.000 --> 00:17:49.080
Trying to make me
break your fucking neck?

256
00:17:50.320 --> 00:17:51.320
[both grunt]

257
00:17:52.640 --> 00:17:55.160
Memorial's about to start.
Don't be so weird.

258
00:17:55.240 --> 00:17:57.320
- You gonna make a speech?
- Are you?

259
00:17:57.400 --> 00:17:59.480
To be honest. I barely remember the guy.

260
00:18:00.080 --> 00:18:01.440
Igor. That was it. right?

261
00:18:01.960 --> 00:18:04.241
- The fuck's wrong with you. Błażej?
- You forget him too.

262
00:18:04.320 --> 00:18:05.960
Don't mention him again. okay?

263
00:18:12.840 --> 00:18:14.736
- Sorry. Doctor. I need you to sign this.
- Later.

264
00:18:14.760 --> 00:18:15.760
Let's go.

265
00:18:16.760 --> 00:18:19.320
[sighs] I don't have much time.
So what do you need?

266
00:18:20.400 --> 00:18:23.240
Guru. "Were you there?" Adam. "No."

267
00:18:23.320 --> 00:18:26.000
Guru. Thumbs-up emoji.
"Coming to the Ranger's party?"

268
00:18:26.080 --> 00:18:28.800
Adam. "Yeah." Adam then says.
"Fuck. man. they're gonna find out."

269
00:18:28.880 --> 00:18:31.640
Guru. "They won't.
Just keep quiet and it'll be okay."

270
00:18:31.720 --> 00:18:32.560
"Keep quiet"?

271
00:18:32.640 --> 00:18:35.480
"Hold tight. It was your fault.
but nobody's gotta know."

272
00:18:36.960 --> 00:18:37.960
Wait a sec.

273
00:18:41.760 --> 00:18:43.880
Who's this guy. "Guru"?
And who's "Ranger"?

274
00:18:44.640 --> 00:18:45.640
I don't know.

275
00:18:48.160 --> 00:18:49.880
"It was your fault"? What does he mean?

276
00:18:49.960 --> 00:18:51.840
I think you know what that means.

277
00:18:52.760 --> 00:18:54.880
That our son is in serious shit right now.

278
00:18:55.960 --> 00:18:57.600
[Anna breathing heavily]

279
00:19:04.960 --> 00:19:06.320
[school bell ringing]

280
00:19:06.400 --> 00:19:08.400
[kids clamoring]

281
00:19:19.720 --> 00:19:21.560
Get out of the bathroom. beard girl.

282
00:19:26.640 --> 00:19:29.080
[bullies laughing]

283
00:19:35.000 --> 00:19:36.800
OLA: WHAT'S UP?

284
00:19:36.880 --> 00:19:39.080
EVERYTHING OK?

285
00:19:39.160 --> 00:19:41.240
WHERE ARE YOU?

286
00:19:41.880 --> 00:19:43.720
HELLO...

287
00:19:43.800 --> 00:19:47.240
JAŚMINA: IN THE SCHOOLYARD

288
00:19:56.240 --> 00:19:57.240
Ola!

289
00:19:59.720 --> 00:20:01.720
[melancholy music playing]

290
00:20:05.520 --> 00:20:06.520
Hey.

291
00:20:07.640 --> 00:20:10.520
- Hey. uh. what happened?
- Nothing.

292
00:20:12.080 --> 00:20:14.360
It's the absolute worst day of my life.

293
00:20:26.560 --> 00:20:28.240
[Jaśmina] <i>What do you want? Just stop it!</i>

294
00:20:35.280 --> 00:20:37.560
- Assholes.
<i>- </i>[Jaśmina] <i>What do you want? Just stop it!</i>

295
00:21:12.880 --> 00:21:14.880
Three Leśna Street
at eight o'clock tonight.

296
00:21:16.000 --> 00:21:17.760
Three Leśna Street
at eight o'clock tonight.

297
00:21:17.840 --> 00:21:19.600
- See you there?
- [girl] Yeah.

298
00:21:19.680 --> 00:21:21.120
Three Leśna Street. tonight.

299
00:21:21.200 --> 00:21:22.920
[Nika's mom]
So those paintings are by Igor?

300
00:21:22.960 --> 00:21:23.960
Yeah.

301
00:21:25.240 --> 00:21:26.800
I guess that's why my Nika was...

302
00:21:27.320 --> 00:21:28.960
Look. Beata came.

303
00:21:30.360 --> 00:21:31.360
[crowd murmuring]

304
00:21:34.680 --> 00:21:35.840
[crowd quiets down]

305
00:21:41.080 --> 00:21:42.680
First her husband. and now this.

306
00:21:45.160 --> 00:21:46.240
Good morning.

307
00:21:46.320 --> 00:21:49.040
Is it true that Igor was
being treated for depression?

308
00:21:49.120 --> 00:21:52.520
Yeah. maybe. I never noticed anything
when he'd come over.

309
00:21:54.000 --> 00:21:57.040
Here's a short video.
Igor's friends made it.

310
00:21:58.600 --> 00:21:59.520
Thank you so much.

311
00:21:59.600 --> 00:22:01.240
Come on. let's go over here.

312
00:22:04.960 --> 00:22:06.160
[woman] Good morning.

313
00:22:06.240 --> 00:22:07.440
Thank you for showing up

314
00:22:07.520 --> 00:22:09.680
in such large numbers
for today's memorial.

315
00:22:11.240 --> 00:22:13.840
My name is Laura Kopińska.

316
00:22:13.920 --> 00:22:17.160
and as most of you probably know.
I'm the school psychologist.

317
00:22:17.760 --> 00:22:22.680
Today. a beloved friend of ours.
Igor Hall. would have turned 18.

318
00:22:23.960 --> 00:22:25.320
He was an exceptional boy.

319
00:22:26.120 --> 00:22:28.080
He was imaginative. sensitive.

320
00:22:29.040 --> 00:22:30.560
and so well-loved.

321
00:22:32.440 --> 00:22:35.640
His friends have put together a video
that we'd like to show you. Thank you.

322
00:22:37.520 --> 00:22:39.440
[Igor whoops. chuckles]

323
00:22:39.520 --> 00:22:40.520
<i>It's beautiful.</i>

324
00:22:41.040 --> 00:22:43.160
["I'll See You in Heaven"
by GrubSon plays]

325
00:22:55.400 --> 00:22:58.000
[in Polish] <i>♪ I'm sure of it ♪</i>

326
00:22:58.080 --> 00:23:00.440
<i>♪ Deep down I know ♪</i>

327
00:23:00.520 --> 00:23:05.480
<i>♪ That one day we will all meet
At the top of a mountain ♪</i>

328
00:23:05.560 --> 00:23:07.440
<i>♪ Even though the world ♪</i>

329
00:23:08.120 --> 00:23:10.280
<i>♪ Which loves us
Hurts us day by day ♪</i>

330
00:23:10.360 --> 00:23:15.280
<i>♪ One day we will all meet
At the top of a mountain ♪</i>

331
00:23:15.360 --> 00:23:17.080
<i>♪ It's ugly
Death awaits us all ♪</i>

332
00:23:17.160 --> 00:23:19.560
<i>♪ Earth craves bodies
Of the human masses ♪</i>

333
00:23:19.640 --> 00:23:22.000
<i>♪ Nobody told us
How long we will live ♪</i>

334
00:23:22.080 --> 00:23:24.520
<i>♪ When the threads of our lives
Will snap ♪</i>

335
00:23:24.600 --> 00:23:27.000
<i>♪ Nobody told us when to say goodbye ♪</i>

336
00:23:27.080 --> 00:23:29.760
<i>♪ And when we are going to meet again ♪</i>

337
00:23:29.840 --> 00:23:31.960
<i>♪ To support and to carry each other ♪</i>

338
00:23:32.040 --> 00:23:34.720
<i>♪ We are born to live
And we live to die ♪</i>

339
00:23:34.800 --> 00:23:39.240
<i>♪ Angel of Death. please tell me
Why don't you care about our suffering ♪</i>

340
00:23:39.320 --> 00:23:41.760
<i>♪ The young are your favorite victims ♪</i>

341
00:23:41.840 --> 00:23:44.440
<i>♪ They haven't hurt you
Yet you mistreat them ♪</i>

342
00:23:44.520 --> 00:23:46.680
<i>♪ See the love inside of us all ♪</i>

343
00:23:46.760 --> 00:23:49.320
<i>♪ We want to live
At least for half a century ♪</i>

344
00:23:49.400 --> 00:23:52.400
<i>♪ A lot of us have lost our friends ♪</i>

345
00:23:52.480 --> 00:23:54.880
<i>♪ It's hard to accept but nevertheless ♪</i>

346
00:23:54.960 --> 00:23:59.760
<i>♪ I'm sure of it
Deep down I know ♪</i>

347
00:23:59.840 --> 00:24:02.280
<i>♪ That one day we will all meet ♪</i>

348
00:24:02.360 --> 00:24:04.800
<i>♪ At the top of a mountain ♪</i>

349
00:24:04.880 --> 00:24:06.640
<i>♪ Even though the world ♪</i>

350
00:24:07.360 --> 00:24:09.720
<i>♪ Which loves us
Hurts us day by day ♪</i>

351
00:24:09.800 --> 00:24:12.040
<i>♪ One day we will all meet ♪</i>

352
00:24:12.120 --> 00:24:14.720
<i>♪ At the top of a mountain ♪</i>

353
00:24:16.080 --> 00:24:17.920
[in English]
<i>You guys better not make fun of me</i>

354
00:24:17.960 --> 00:24:21.240
<i>for what I'm...
um. for what I'm about to say.</i>

355
00:24:21.320 --> 00:24:22.520
<i>It's dumb.</i>

356
00:24:22.600 --> 00:24:23.840
<i>Uh...</i>

357
00:24:23.920 --> 00:24:24.920
<i>I miss you.</i>

358
00:24:26.160 --> 00:24:28.320
<i>I'm back in a week.
so as soon as I'm there.</i>

359
00:24:28.400 --> 00:24:29.960
<i>I wanna hang out with everyone.</i>

360
00:24:30.040 --> 00:24:31.040
<i>See you guys.</i>

361
00:24:41.040 --> 00:24:42.040
Hop in.

362
00:24:43.800 --> 00:24:47.400
- Beata. you know you can come to us...
- Don't act like you care about my family!

363
00:24:47.480 --> 00:24:49.400
Everyone acts like nothing happened.

364
00:24:49.480 --> 00:24:51.320
They dragged him into that shit!

365
00:24:52.800 --> 00:24:53.960
Why my son?

366
00:24:54.480 --> 00:24:58.160
Tell me. why did it have to be my son?
Just talk to me!

367
00:24:58.240 --> 00:25:00.521
- Get in the car.
- Why'd you put those ideas in his head?

368
00:25:00.960 --> 00:25:02.200
- Ms. Hall...
- Speak!

369
00:25:02.760 --> 00:25:04.840
It's a terrible loss.
and I'm deeply sorry.

370
00:25:04.920 --> 00:25:07.920
And you. Adam. you're also responsible.

371
00:25:08.000 --> 00:25:10.120
Where the hell were you
when he needed you?

372
00:25:11.360 --> 00:25:12.800
You know Igor loved you.

373
00:25:12.880 --> 00:25:15.120
How could you let this happen
to your friend?

374
00:25:15.200 --> 00:25:17.400
[car engine revs]

375
00:25:17.480 --> 00:25:19.600
[intense music playing]

376
00:25:45.000 --> 00:25:46.480
[Adam] Hey. come on. get him!

377
00:25:53.440 --> 00:25:55.560
- [Adam] Damn it!
- [player groans]

378
00:25:57.080 --> 00:25:58.480
Hey. pass the ball! Ah!

379
00:25:58.560 --> 00:26:00.200
- Hey!
- That one's mine.

380
00:26:00.280 --> 00:26:01.280
Block it. Igor!

381
00:26:03.160 --> 00:26:06.120
[player whoops] Yeah!
That's what I'm talking about.

382
00:26:12.000 --> 00:26:13.000
[pants] Good job.

383
00:26:22.760 --> 00:26:23.760
I'm here for you.

384
00:26:25.960 --> 00:26:27.800
You can talk to me about everything.

385
00:26:31.920 --> 00:26:33.400
Hey. man. cut it out!

386
00:26:38.760 --> 00:26:41.000
I know Igor's passing
has been hard on you.

387
00:26:42.360 --> 00:26:43.960
It's been hard on all of us.

388
00:26:44.040 --> 00:26:45.440
Jesus. Mom...

389
00:26:47.800 --> 00:26:49.080
Why do you talk to me like that?

390
00:26:49.880 --> 00:26:51.440
Okay. just drop me off here.

391
00:26:53.400 --> 00:26:54.600
I thought you had practice.

392
00:26:54.680 --> 00:26:56.320
I'm gonna jump out
if you don't pull over.

393
00:26:56.360 --> 00:26:57.440
Calm down!

394
00:26:57.520 --> 00:26:58.880
Don't yell at me. okay?

395
00:26:59.880 --> 00:27:01.480
[seat belt alert beeps]

396
00:27:05.320 --> 00:27:07.560
Remember to come straight home afterwards.

397
00:27:10.760 --> 00:27:12.760
[intense music continuing]

398
00:27:24.040 --> 00:27:28.240
Pray for us sinners.
now and at the hour of our death. Amen.

399
00:27:28.320 --> 00:27:31.360
Hail Mary. full of grace.
the Lord is with thee.

400
00:27:31.440 --> 00:27:33.480
Blessed are thou among women.

401
00:27:33.560 --> 00:27:36.000
and blessed is the fruit
of thy womb. Jesus.

402
00:27:38.920 --> 00:27:42.040
And please. release me from this anger.

403
00:28:00.200 --> 00:28:02.200
[melancholy music playing]

404
00:28:17.000 --> 00:28:18.320
[music turns suspenseful]

405
00:28:27.920 --> 00:28:28.920
Sophia?

406
00:28:30.960 --> 00:28:31.960
Come here for a sec.

407
00:28:32.720 --> 00:28:34.720
Hanna. go to Igor's room
and get the box of photos.

408
00:28:34.760 --> 00:28:36.600
The gray one with the numbers on it.

409
00:28:37.600 --> 00:28:39.040
Remember the day Igor died?

410
00:28:39.120 --> 00:28:41.200
In the morning. he scratched himself.

411
00:28:41.280 --> 00:28:43.840
You put a Band-Aid on him
and you laughed. remember?

412
00:28:44.320 --> 00:28:46.320
Ah. the photo was taken before that.

413
00:28:51.960 --> 00:28:52.960
Where is it?

414
00:28:59.520 --> 00:29:00.720
Is this the same hoodie?

415
00:29:01.800 --> 00:29:02.800
You think it is?

416
00:29:03.920 --> 00:29:05.120
Hanna. come and look.

417
00:29:07.920 --> 00:29:09.400
Is it the same hoodie or not?

418
00:29:09.480 --> 00:29:10.480
- Yes.
- Yes.

419
00:29:11.760 --> 00:29:13.000
So he wasn't alone.

420
00:29:15.800 --> 00:29:17.200
- It's Monday. right?
- Mm-hmm.

421
00:29:18.840 --> 00:29:21.000
Girls. I need you to stay here.

422
00:29:21.080 --> 00:29:22.720
Don't answer the door if anyone comes.

423
00:29:22.800 --> 00:29:23.800
I'll be right back.

424
00:29:26.520 --> 00:29:27.520
[players chattering]

425
00:29:33.920 --> 00:29:34.920
[Adam] Pass it!

426
00:29:37.320 --> 00:29:38.880
[excited chatter]

427
00:29:39.640 --> 00:29:40.640
[boy 1] Yes!

428
00:29:49.520 --> 00:29:50.680
[boy 2] Go. go. go!

429
00:29:50.760 --> 00:29:51.960
[boy 1] Grab him!

430
00:29:52.040 --> 00:29:53.720
[overlapping chatter]

431
00:29:55.200 --> 00:29:56.360
[boy 2] Hey. get on D!

432
00:29:56.440 --> 00:29:58.640
- Barczyk. where are you going?
- Five minutes.

433
00:29:59.160 --> 00:30:00.440
[boy 1] Where you going?

434
00:30:01.800 --> 00:30:02.800
[boy 2] Yo. Adam!

435
00:30:03.280 --> 00:30:04.200
What's this about?

436
00:30:04.280 --> 00:30:06.520
I see you've taken Igor's place
on the court.

437
00:30:11.000 --> 00:30:13.840
I always scheduled my Mondays
around your practice.

438
00:30:16.680 --> 00:30:18.040
I could never replace Igor.

439
00:30:20.320 --> 00:30:21.360
He was the best.

440
00:30:23.640 --> 00:30:24.840
Do you miss him?

441
00:30:27.160 --> 00:30:28.240
Of course.

442
00:30:28.760 --> 00:30:30.560
Then why didn't you do anything?

443
00:30:33.680 --> 00:30:36.040
Adam. I know you were there with him.

444
00:30:37.320 --> 00:30:39.280
How could you just let him die?

445
00:30:39.360 --> 00:30:40.840
Who the hell told you that?

446
00:30:40.920 --> 00:30:43.680
- I saw the picture.
- What do you mean. the picture?

447
00:30:44.280 --> 00:30:46.600
Adam. can you please just tell me
what happened that night?

448
00:30:46.640 --> 00:30:48.720
Please. tell me what happened.

449
00:30:48.800 --> 00:30:50.400
Adam.

450
00:30:50.480 --> 00:30:51.960
I'm going to tell the police.

451
00:31:02.200 --> 00:31:04.200
What am I supposed to be seeing here?

452
00:31:04.280 --> 00:31:07.240
You can see my son Igor.
Igor and his friend Adam.

453
00:31:07.320 --> 00:31:09.240
who's wearing the same hoodie
you can see here.

454
00:31:10.880 --> 00:31:13.120
Here Igor has a Band-Aid on his forehead.

455
00:31:13.200 --> 00:31:15.960
I put it on him
after he hit his head that morning.

456
00:31:16.040 --> 00:31:17.080
- Morning?
- Yes.

457
00:31:17.160 --> 00:31:20.560
This photo was taken the day he died.
and this one before his death.

458
00:31:20.640 --> 00:31:24.200
You can see it. It's the same hoodie
that Adam Barczyk is wearing.

459
00:31:24.280 --> 00:31:27.240
You have to question him.
I'm sure he was involved.

460
00:31:27.320 --> 00:31:29.360
At the time of his death.
your son was alone. ma'am.

461
00:31:29.440 --> 00:31:31.400
We've already ruled out foul play.

462
00:31:31.480 --> 00:31:33.120
The case is closed. I'm sorry.

463
00:31:40.080 --> 00:31:41.160
Do you have kids?

464
00:31:42.440 --> 00:31:43.440
Yes. I do.

465
00:31:45.320 --> 00:31:46.440
Do you love them?

466
00:31:48.360 --> 00:31:49.280
Mmm.

467
00:31:49.360 --> 00:31:52.560
I know my son had been drinking
and I know he was taking drugs.

468
00:31:53.520 --> 00:31:57.040
But I'm begging you to at least
talk to Adam Barczyk. At least do that.

469
00:31:58.720 --> 00:32:00.240
I'm asking you as a parent.

470
00:32:01.840 --> 00:32:03.160
[tense music playing]

471
00:32:03.240 --> 00:32:04.240
[sighs]

472
00:32:08.440 --> 00:32:10.000
[line beeps]

473
00:32:10.080 --> 00:32:11.200
His mom won't drop it.

474
00:32:12.640 --> 00:32:14.400
This won't just disappear.

475
00:32:19.280 --> 00:32:21.280
[mellow pop music playing in bar]

476
00:32:27.840 --> 00:32:30.520
Sorry to bother you.
I'm looking for someone.

477
00:32:30.600 --> 00:32:32.520
[laughs] Aren't we all. though?

478
00:32:32.600 --> 00:32:34.520
It's someone who comes here often.

479
00:32:35.040 --> 00:32:37.480
Here. Please. could you take a look?

480
00:32:41.440 --> 00:32:43.280
Nah. I haven't seen her around.

481
00:32:45.960 --> 00:32:46.960
How about this?

482
00:32:48.560 --> 00:32:49.560
Nope.

483
00:33:00.640 --> 00:33:02.040
- Hey.
- Hey. honey.

484
00:33:02.120 --> 00:33:04.120
Wait. Come here.

485
00:33:04.200 --> 00:33:06.640
- [Ola] <i>Do we have math tomorrow?</i>
- Wanna say hi?

486
00:33:07.160 --> 00:33:08.680
<i>Should I bring my books?</i>

487
00:33:10.360 --> 00:33:11.800
- Hi. Ola.
<i>- Hi. Hello.</i>

488
00:33:12.520 --> 00:33:13.600
Are you coming today?

489
00:33:13.680 --> 00:33:16.640
- I spoke to your mom this morning.
<i>- Yeah. I'm coming later.</i>

490
00:33:16.720 --> 00:33:18.240
<i>I have swimming class now.</i>

491
00:33:18.320 --> 00:33:20.400
I'm gonna make paella.
I got all the ingredients.

492
00:33:20.480 --> 00:33:22.480
- Rice. vegetables...
- Fire extinguisher.

493
00:33:23.080 --> 00:33:23.920
<i>What?</i>

494
00:33:24.000 --> 00:33:26.400
Last time he tried to cook.
he set off the fire alarm.

495
00:33:26.480 --> 00:33:27.760
Didn't I tell you that?

496
00:33:27.840 --> 00:33:30.160
Hey. at least I always
keep you entertained.

497
00:33:30.240 --> 00:33:31.760
- Hey! [laughs]
- [phone ringing]

498
00:33:35.760 --> 00:33:36.840
[ringing]

499
00:33:48.000 --> 00:33:49.000
Hey. Renata.

500
00:33:49.960 --> 00:33:51.240
You still have my number?

501
00:33:51.320 --> 00:33:53.400
Hi. Uh. I know
I shouldn't be calling you.

502
00:33:53.480 --> 00:33:56.320
I'm... looking for Marianna.

503
00:33:57.080 --> 00:33:59.480
I've been trying
to get ahold of her for days.

504
00:33:59.560 --> 00:34:00.840
It's like she disappeared.

505
00:34:01.960 --> 00:34:05.800
We're no longer in contact.
She doesn't give a shit about us.

506
00:34:05.880 --> 00:34:08.000
Listen. it's not like that.

507
00:34:08.080 --> 00:34:10.160
She just... She really misses Jaśmina.

508
00:34:10.240 --> 00:34:12.720
but... she just got a little lost.

509
00:34:13.320 --> 00:34:14.440
<i>I'm worried about her.</i>

510
00:34:14.960 --> 00:34:16.960
Hmm. And I'm worried about my daughter.

511
00:34:18.400 --> 00:34:21.240
<i>Okay. Janusz. you think
I want to have this conversation now?</i>

512
00:34:24.280 --> 00:34:26.560
That's exactly what she said
when she left me.

513
00:34:27.160 --> 00:34:28.680
<i>Don't call me again about her.</i>

514
00:34:29.360 --> 00:34:30.360
[grunts]

515
00:34:34.640 --> 00:34:35.640
[exhales]

516
00:34:37.560 --> 00:34:39.880
I know I look hot.
but I can't breathe in this.

517
00:34:39.960 --> 00:34:42.400
I don't think
you could've gone any tighter.

518
00:34:42.480 --> 00:34:43.480
Maybe shorter.

519
00:34:45.120 --> 00:34:46.120
What's up with you?

520
00:34:46.160 --> 00:34:48.720
Adam's been acting weird.
and he's not texting back.

521
00:34:48.800 --> 00:34:50.360
I know he's done with practice.

522
00:34:50.440 --> 00:34:52.640
Relax. He's gonna be at Gajos's thing.

523
00:34:53.400 --> 00:34:55.400
- Hi. how are you?
- [driver] Good evening.

524
00:35:03.520 --> 00:35:05.160
[Polish hip-hop playing]

525
00:35:05.240 --> 00:35:07.360
<i>Hey. this is Adam. Leave a message.</i>

526
00:35:09.680 --> 00:35:11.120
Come on. Kaja.

527
00:35:11.200 --> 00:35:13.200
[singer singing in Polish]

528
00:35:30.440 --> 00:35:31.520
- Hey.
- [girls] Hey.

529
00:35:31.600 --> 00:35:33.320
- The ladies have arrived.
- Hi. Błażej.

530
00:35:33.400 --> 00:35:34.400
How's it going?

531
00:35:35.120 --> 00:35:36.120
Hey. girl.

532
00:35:37.520 --> 00:35:38.720
Entry fee.

533
00:35:38.800 --> 00:35:40.000
- There you go.
- Pay up.

534
00:35:41.760 --> 00:35:42.800
[chuckles]

535
00:35:45.760 --> 00:35:47.240
- Where's Adam?
- I don't know.

536
00:35:47.320 --> 00:35:49.080
- He said he'd be here.
- He's not.

537
00:35:59.920 --> 00:36:01.320
[boy] Thanks. man. Cheers.

538
00:36:08.240 --> 00:36:09.520
Hey. dude. where are you?

539
00:36:09.600 --> 00:36:10.760
You said you'd be here.

540
00:36:23.480 --> 00:36:24.920
[party-goers cough]

541
00:36:32.560 --> 00:36:33.840
[Gajos] Hey. Adam!

542
00:36:33.920 --> 00:36:36.600
- [party-goers clamoring]
- Are you out of your mind?

543
00:36:36.680 --> 00:36:37.520
[girl] The fuck?

544
00:36:37.600 --> 00:36:38.640
Are you?

545
00:36:38.720 --> 00:36:40.240
[party-goers angrily murmur]

546
00:36:40.320 --> 00:36:42.400
You're all in mourning. I can tell.

547
00:36:42.480 --> 00:36:43.720
Still grieving.

548
00:36:44.880 --> 00:36:46.440
None of you give a shit about Igor.

549
00:36:46.520 --> 00:36:47.960
Igor? Igor's gone now.

550
00:36:48.040 --> 00:36:49.960
and we don't talk about him. remember?

551
00:36:50.040 --> 00:36:51.600
Not right now. and not ever.

552
00:36:51.680 --> 00:36:52.720
Get the fuck off!

553
00:36:53.840 --> 00:36:55.320
His mom's been talking to the police.

554
00:36:56.160 --> 00:36:59.360
It's all over. Gajos.
Whether you want to believe it or not.

555
00:37:01.000 --> 00:37:02.000
[Kaja] Adam.

556
00:37:04.440 --> 00:37:06.480
Get everyone out of here before 10:00.

557
00:37:08.040 --> 00:37:09.560
Wait. I'm coming with you.

558
00:37:17.760 --> 00:37:18.760
You can't.

559
00:37:20.800 --> 00:37:21.800
I'm really sorry.

560
00:37:27.160 --> 00:37:29.160
[tense music builds]

561
00:37:30.800 --> 00:37:32.000
Don't stay up too late.

562
00:37:32.080 --> 00:37:33.800
Hey! Hey. hey. hey.

563
00:37:35.480 --> 00:37:36.560
- Bye.
- [phone ringing]

564
00:37:36.640 --> 00:37:37.640
Bye.

565
00:37:43.280 --> 00:37:46.360
I'm on my way home.
Ola and Jaśmina are having a sleepover.

566
00:37:46.440 --> 00:37:49.280
Great. Listen. I got a call.
and I'm headed to Szczecin.

567
00:37:49.360 --> 00:37:50.800
<i>Because of the fire at that factory?</i>

568
00:37:50.840 --> 00:37:52.680
<i>- I heard about it on the news.</i>
- Yeah.

569
00:37:52.760 --> 00:37:55.280
The local office can't manage it.
I have a flight in 30 minutes.

570
00:37:55.320 --> 00:37:58.600
<i>- I'll be back tomorrow. probably.</i>
- Adam came home from practice. right?

571
00:37:58.680 --> 00:38:00.920
<i>I don't know. He wasn't back when I left.</i>

572
00:38:01.000 --> 00:38:02.600
<i>He's probably with his friends.</i>

573
00:38:03.440 --> 00:38:04.680
Love you. Take care.

574
00:38:04.760 --> 00:38:05.840
<i>You too. Bye.</i>

575
00:38:05.920 --> 00:38:07.920
[tense music playing]

576
00:38:22.760 --> 00:38:23.760
Adam?

577
00:38:25.360 --> 00:38:26.360
Adam?

578
00:38:27.920 --> 00:38:28.920
[phone chimes]

579
00:38:33.600 --> 00:38:37.760
GURU: WHERE ARE YOU?

580
00:38:37.840 --> 00:38:40.280
AT GAJEWICZ'S PARTY?

581
00:38:40.360 --> 00:38:41.360
Adam?

582
00:38:46.080 --> 00:38:48.160
<i>Hey. this is Adam. Leave a message.</i>

583
00:38:48.800 --> 00:38:50.640
- [beep]
- Adam. where are you?

584
00:38:50.720 --> 00:38:52.240
Please call me back right away

585
00:39:04.120 --> 00:39:05.160
Hi. Sorry.

586
00:39:07.240 --> 00:39:09.120
It's pretty late. Is something wrong?

587
00:39:10.080 --> 00:39:11.960
- Adam's here with you?
- No.

588
00:39:12.040 --> 00:39:14.280
You sure? Your son was having a party.

589
00:39:15.320 --> 00:39:16.560
Do you hear any music?

590
00:39:17.160 --> 00:39:18.280
They were texting.

591
00:39:18.360 --> 00:39:19.640
How do you know?

592
00:39:20.960 --> 00:39:21.960
Could I come in?

593
00:39:23.440 --> 00:39:24.280
It's very late.

594
00:39:24.360 --> 00:39:26.360
I know. but it's really important.

595
00:39:26.440 --> 00:39:28.760
Maybe you wanna try
calling your son. then.

596
00:39:31.480 --> 00:39:32.480
Okay.

597
00:39:46.000 --> 00:39:47.800
<i>Hey. this is Adam. Leave a message.</i>

598
00:39:47.880 --> 00:39:49.160
[beep]

599
00:39:49.240 --> 00:39:51.400
Please call back when you can.
I'm worried.

600
00:39:51.480 --> 00:39:53.680
Hi. Kaja. Where are you right now?

601
00:39:53.760 --> 00:39:55.960
I'm at this party now.
but Adam took off.

602
00:39:56.040 --> 00:39:57.680
and I don't know where he went.

603
00:39:59.880 --> 00:40:01.440
<i>He just had a fight with Gajos.</i>

604
00:40:03.320 --> 00:40:04.160
Over what?

605
00:40:04.240 --> 00:40:05.240
<i>I don't know.</i>

606
00:40:08.440 --> 00:40:10.440
Mmm. do you know where he could've gone?

607
00:40:10.520 --> 00:40:12.680
<i>To be honest. I really have no idea.</i>

608
00:40:12.760 --> 00:40:15.440
<i>Maybe he's at our usual spot
over at the beach.</i>

609
00:40:16.040 --> 00:40:19.440
Mmm. Okay. thanks. I won't take up
any more of your time. Night.

610
00:40:19.520 --> 00:40:20.520
<i>Good night.</i>

611
00:40:23.960 --> 00:40:24.960
[sighs]

612
00:40:39.560 --> 00:40:41.560
[music turns foreboding]

613
00:40:50.720 --> 00:40:51.880
[indistinct chattering]

614
00:41:28.960 --> 00:41:30.960
[mysterious music playing]

615
00:42:19.240 --> 00:42:21.240
[mysterious music continuing]

616
00:42:39.840 --> 00:42:41.840
[passersby chattering]

617
00:42:58.280 --> 00:42:59.280
[wheels clatter]

618
00:43:07.520 --> 00:43:09.520
[indistinct chattering]

619
00:43:32.640 --> 00:43:34.200
Hey. what are doing here?

620
00:43:34.280 --> 00:43:35.440
I'm looking for my son.

621
00:43:36.040 --> 00:43:38.000
- You seen him?
- [bouncer] What's up?

622
00:43:42.160 --> 00:43:44.280
Please let me in. My son's in there.

623
00:43:44.360 --> 00:43:45.520
It's a private party.

624
00:43:46.280 --> 00:43:48.120
Come on. let me in. Why do you care?

625
00:43:48.200 --> 00:43:49.400
No. I don't care at all.

626
00:43:49.480 --> 00:43:52.280
Now fuck off
before I start to lose my patience.

627
00:43:53.920 --> 00:43:55.320
[man] Anna. just drop it.

628
00:43:55.400 --> 00:43:56.400
Just go back home.

629
00:44:02.400 --> 00:44:04.400
[dramatic music playing]

630
00:44:43.520 --> 00:44:46.440
Have you seen a teen here
wearing a red hat and a backpack?

631
00:44:48.640 --> 00:44:49.800
[tense music playing]

632
00:44:51.560 --> 00:44:52.960
[grunting]

633
00:45:23.040 --> 00:45:24.040
[grunts]

634
00:45:29.600 --> 00:45:31.240
- [grunts]
- [music stops abruptly]

635
00:45:35.200 --> 00:45:37.280
[truck beeping]

636
00:45:54.040 --> 00:45:55.200
Oh. fuck.

637
00:46:13.840 --> 00:46:15.840
[tense outro music playing]

638
00:46:16.305 --> 00:47:16.266
